# Sigma Research Skill

Conduct current-year-aware web research using MCP tools, curate credible sources.

## Tool Preferences

Try in order:
1. `mcp_exa_web_search_exa` - Technical/code content
2. `mcp_perplexity-ask_perplexity_ask` - Conversational research
3. `mcp_Ref_ref_search_documentation` - Library/framework docs

## Workflow

### 1. Build Year-Aware Queries

Always include current year:
```javascript
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
const queries = [
  `${topic} best practices ${year}`,
  `${topic} vs alternatives ${year}`,
];
```

### 2. Evaluate Source Credibility

| Factor | Weight | Criteria |
|--------|--------|----------|
| Recency | 30% | Within 12 months |
| Authority | 25% | Expert, official docs |
| Relevance | 25% | Directly addresses query |
| Depth | 20% | Actionable detail |

Discard sources scoring below 60%.

### 3. Output Format

```markdown
# Research: {Topic}

**Date:** {TODAY}
**Sources Evaluated:** {N}
**Sources Included:** {M}

## Executive Summary
{2-3 paragraph synthesis}

## Key Findings

### Finding 1: {Title}
{Description with data}
*Source: [Title](URL)*

## Source List
| # | Title | URL | Credibility |
|---|-------|-----|-------------|
| 1 | ... | ... | 85% |
```

## Quality Gates

- [ ] At least 5 credible sources
- [ ] All sources from within 18 months
- [ ] Conflicting findings noted
- [ ] Executive summary synthesizes (not lists)
